---
description: Security best practices for the PDD project
globs: "**/*.py"
alwaysApply: false
---
- Never hardcode API keys or sensitive information in code
- Use keyring for secure credential storage when appropriate
- Sanitize user inputs before processing
- Validate file paths to prevent path traversal issues
- Use secure defaults for all configurable options
- Be cautious with executing user-provided code or commands
- Limit file permissions when creating new files
